  "prompt": "What should we think while meditating?",
  "response": "During meditation, the goal is typically not to think actively, but rather to observe your thoughts without judgment. Here are some approaches:\n\n1. Mindfulness meditation:\n- Focus on your breath\n- Observe thoughts as they come and go\n- Let thoughts pass without engaging with them\n- Return attention to breathing when mind wanders\n\n2. Mantra meditation:\n- Repeat a calming word or phrase\n- Use the mantra to anchor your concentration\n- Let other thoughts drift away\n\n3. Body scan meditation:\n- Pay attention to physical sensations\n- Move awareness slowly through different body parts\n- Notice sensations without judgment\n\n4. Loving-kindness meditation:\n- Focus on generating feelings of compassion\n- Send positive thoughts to yourself and others\n- Cultivate feelings of warmth and goodwill\n\n5. Guided meditation:\n- Follow a teacher's instructions\n- Visualize peaceful scenes\n- Focus on specific thoughts or intentions\n\nKey principles:\n- Don't force thoughts away\n- Be gentle with yourself\n- Accept whatever arises\n- Aim for non-judgmental awareness\n- Practice returning to your focal point\n\nThe goal is not to eliminate thinking, but to develop a different relationship with your thoughts, creating space and reducing reactivity.",
